The paper deals with a communication task in a network, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of beeps for communication in a wireless network suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The study of deterministic algorithms for broadcasting in a weak model of wireless communication is related to Self-Organizing Systems (cs.SI). The analysis of the cost of broadcasting algorithms involves the study of algorithms and data structures, which falls under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the study of different levels of knowledge that nodes may have about the network suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AL).
